| Numbers/XS-Strikethrough | Azeret Mono | 14px | 400 | 1.2 | 0 | Crossed-out prices |

### SCSS Typography Pattern

```scss
// Display headline (STIX Two Text)
.section-title {
    font-family: $STIX-Two-Text;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 54px;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -1.08px;
    color: $color-black;

    @media #{$medium-screen-and-smaller} {
        font-size: 36px;
        letter-spacing: -0.72px;
    }
}

// Body text (DM Sans)
.body-text {
    font-family: $DM-Sans;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.4;
    letter-spacing: -0.16px;
    color: $color-black;
}

// Stat number (Azeret Mono)
.stat-number {
    font-family: $Azeret-Mono;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 60px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: $color-black;
}

// Button text (DM Sans Medium)
.cta-button {
    font-family: $DM-Sans;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 24px;
    letter-spacing: 0.8px;
}
```

## Spacing System

### Section Padding (from Figma)

| Context | Desktop | Tablet | Mobile |
|---------|---------|--------|--------|
| Section horizontal padding | 64px | 32px | 15px |
| Section vertical padding | 64-80px | 40-56px | 22.5-40px |
| Card internal padding | 16px | 16px | 16px |
| Content gap (large) | 40-80px | 32-40px | 15-24px |
| Content gap (medium) | 24-32px | 16-24px | 15-16px |
| Content gap (small) | 8-16px | 8-16px | 8px |
| Card gap | 24px | 24px | 16px |

### SCSS Spacing Pattern

```scss
.section {
    padding: 80px 64px;

    @media #{$medium-screen-and-smaller} {
        padding: 56px 32px;
    }

    @media #{$small-screen-and-smaller} {
        padding: 40px 15px;
    }
}
```

## Shadows

### Soft Shadow (Cards)
```scss
// Figma: "Soft Shadow"
box-shadow:
    0px 4px 10px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.09),
    0px 18px 18px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.07),
    0px 40px 24px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04),
    0px 71px 28px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.01),
    0px 111px 31px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);
```

### Quiz Answer Shadow
```scss
// Figma: Quiz answer buttons
box-shadow:
    0px 3px 6px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1),
    0px 10px 10px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.09),
    0px 23px 14px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05),
    0px 40px 16px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.01),
    0px 63px 18px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);
```

## Border Radius

| Element | Radius |
|---------|--------|
| CTA buttons | 2px |
| Stat/Review cards | 15px |
| Step number circles | 1000px (full circle) |
| Arrow navigation buttons | 40px (pill shape) |
| Card images | 8px |

## Component Patterns

### CTA Button
```scss
.cta-button {
    background-color: $color-yellow;
    color: $color-black;
    font-family: $DM-Sans;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 24px;
    letter-spacing: 0.8px;
    padding: 12px 32px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-decoration: none;

    &:hover {
        background-color: $color-yellow-dark;
    }
}
```

### Dark CTA Button (Quiz Selected Answer)
```scss
.quiz-answer-selected {
    background-color: $color-black;
    color: $color-white;
    // Same font/padding as primary CTA
}
```

### Trustpilot Badge Row
```
Structure: "Excellent" text | Star rating SVG | "X,XXX reviews on" text | Trustpilot logo
Font: DM Sans, 12px, regular
All elements inline-flex, vertically centered, 8px gap
```

## Image Conventions

### Hero Images
- Desktop: Side-by-side with text (50/50 split, 720px each at 1440px viewport)
- Tablet: Stacked — image on top, full width (768px)
- Mobile: Stacked — image on top, full width (393px)
- Use `object-fit: cover` for responsive sizing
- Format: `.webp` preferred

### Review/Card Images
- Aspect ratio: 16:9 (352×198 at card width)
- `object-fit: cover`
- Border-radius: 0 (flush with card edges)

### Step/How-It-Works Images
- Border-radius: 8px
- Numbered badge overlay: 56px circle, yellow background, positioned top-left 16px inset

### Listicle Images
- Fixed height: 416px
- Width: ~48% of viewport (688px at 1440px)
- `object-fit: cover`
- Alternating left/right layout (odd items: text left, image right)

