## Carousel Pattern (Direct Slick)

New-style templates call Slick directly rather than using `initCarousel`. This is the preferred pattern on opt-longevity and similar pages.

### PHP — nav uses `navigation-wrapper` + `slick-dots` container

```php
<div class="[prefix]-carousel">
    <?php foreach ($items as $item): ?>
    <div class="[item-class]">...</div>
    <?php endforeach; ?>
</div>
<div class="navigation-wrapper [prefix]-navigation">
    <div class="previous">
        <button type="button" class="[prefix]-prev">
            <img src="<?php echo $theme_folder; ?>/static/media/images/icons/arrow-circle_left.svg"
                 alt="Arrow pointing left" width="48" height="48" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        </button>
    </div>
    <div class="nav-dots [prefix]-dots"></div>
    <div class="next">
        <button type="button" class="[prefix]-next">
            <img src="<?php echo $theme_folder; ?>/static/media/images/icons/arrow-circle_right.svg"
                 alt="Arrow pointing right" width="48" height="48" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        </button>
    </div>
</div>
```

The `.navigation-wrapper` styles (arrows, dot layout) come from `src/static/scss/parts/carousel-navigation.scss` which is included globally via `main.scss`.

### SCSS — inline Slick core + aria-hidden fix + dots

```scss
.[prefix]-carousel {
    overflow-x: hidden;
    overflow-y: visible;
    width: 100%;

    // Slick core (must be inlined per-carousel)
    .slick-list {
        overflow: hidden;
        display: block;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        &.dragging img { pointer-events: none; }
    }
    .slick-track {
        display: flex !important;
        align-items: stretch;
        margin: auto;
    }
    .slick-slide {
        height: inherit;
        > div { height: 100%; }

        // CRITICAL: override global [aria-hidden="true"] { display: none !important }
        // Slick sets aria-hidden on off-screen slides; clipping is done by
        // .slick-list overflow:hidden — do NOT hide slides with display:none.
        // Only needed for infinite: true carousels (clones get aria-hidden="true").
        &[aria-hidden="true"] {
            display: block !important;
        }
    }
    .slick-initialized .[item-class] {
        display: flex !important;
    }
}

.[prefix]-dots {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    min-width: fonts.rem(84px);

    // Slick appendDots generates <ul class="slick-dots"> NOT .nav-dot buttons.
    .slick-dots {
        list-style: none;
        padding: 0;
        margin: 0;
        display: flex !important;
        align-items: center;
        gap: fonts.rem(8px);
        position: static;
        bottom: auto;

        li {
            margin: 0;
            width: auto;
            height: auto;
            line-height: 0;

            button {
                width: 12px;
                height: 12px;
                border-radius: 50%;
                background-color: rgba(96, 91, 82, 0.3);
                border: none;
                padding: 0;
                cursor: pointer;
                font-size: 0;    // hides the number Slick puts in the button
                line-height: 0;
                transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
                &::before { display: none; }
            }
            &.slick-active button {
                background-color: colors.$color-black;
            }
        }
    }
}
```

### JS

```javascript
function init[Prefix]Carousel() {
    if (typeof jQuery === 'undefined' || typeof jQuery.fn.slick === 'undefined') return;
    const $ = jQuery;
    const $carousel = $('.[prefix]-carousel');
    if (!$carousel.length) return;

    $carousel.slick({
        slidesToShow: 3,
        infinite: true,
        centerMode: true,
        centerPadding: '0px',
        dots: true,
        appendDots: '.[section] .[prefix]-dots',
        arrows: false,
        accessibility: false,  // disables tab/arrow nav, NOT aria-hidden — see SCSS note
        responsive: [
            {
                breakpoint: 1025,
                settings: {
                    slidesToShow: 1,
                    centerMode: true,
                    centerPadding: '40px',
                    accessibility: false,
                },
            },
        ],
    });

    $('.[prefix]-prev').on('click', function () { $carousel.slick('slickPrev'); });
    $('.[prefix]-next').on('click', function () { $carousel.slick('slickNext'); });
}
```

### Critical: `accessibility: false` does NOT prevent aria-hidden

`accessibility: false` only disables keyboard tab/arrow navigation. Slick **still sets `aria-hidden="true"`** on non-visible slides with `infinite: true`. The global CSS has `[aria-hidden="true"] { display: none !important }` which kills those slides visually. Always add the `.slick-slide[aria-hidden="true"] { display: block !important }` override in the carousel's SCSS block.

**Safe carousels** (no override needed): `infinite: false` — no clones are created, all slides stay `aria-hidden="false"`.

